{"id":3,"date":"2023-02-25T17:28:32","date_gmt":"2023-02-25T17:28:32","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/estacisity.wtf\/tgmodz\/?page_id=3"},"modified":"2023-12-29T20:33:55","modified_gmt":"2023-12-29T15:03:55","slug":"privacy-policy","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/tgmodz.com\/privacy-policy\/","title":{"rendered":"Privacy Policy"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"3\" class=\"elementor elementor-3\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-56e05eac elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"56e05eac\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-324beff8\" data-id=\"324beff8\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c9edec8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c9edec8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Cookies<\/h2>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Cookies are text files placed on your computer to collect standard Internet log information and visitor behavior information. When you visit our websites, we may collect information from you automatically through cookies or similar technology. For further information, visit allaboutcookies.org. If you leave a comment on TGModz you may save your name, email address and website in cookies. These cookies are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year. If you visit our login page, TGModz will send a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser. When you log in, TGModz will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &#8220;Remember Me&#8221;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed. If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day. You can set your browser not to accept cookies, However, in a few cases, some of our website features may not function as a result.<\/p>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Media<\/h2>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">If you upload media to TGModz, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included or any other personal information. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website. TGModz is NOT responsible for regulating media which is uploaded to the site.<\/p>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Payments<\/h2>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">TGModz uses third party payments in order to bill and process any payments and subscriptions made via TGModz. These parties will request you to disclose sensitive information with them in order to complete purchases and verify purchases. Such third-party payment processing platforms are governed by their own safety standards, policies and terms of use. TGModz picks third party payment processing platforms with extreme caution to protect user privacy, TGModz tries their upmost to stay up to date with their operations and practices. TGModz urges users to practice online safety measures in order to protect their financial information.<\/p>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Data<\/h2>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">You directly provide TGModz with most of the data we collect. TGModz collects data and processes data when you: Register online or place an order for any of TGModz products or services. Voluntarily complete a customer survey or provide feedback on any of our message boards or via email. Use or view TGModz via your browser&#8217;s cookies. TGModz securely stores your data with WordPress and WooCommerce in a secure database which is encrypted by a secure password. TGModz uses a secure HTTPS connection and SSL cert to your client. Strong encryption is used to ensure your privacy and security. We encrypt (serve over SSL) , data sent to and from https:\/\/tgmodz.com only. We consider strong encryption so important that we do not offer the option to disable it, which would compromise the security of your data on TGModz. We also 301 redirect all insecure HTTP requests to the secure HTTPS version. TGModz runs firewalls and have processes in place to alert us about unauthorized attempts to access TGModz accounts. TGModz is continuously watching web traffic and monitoring suspicious activity. TGModz also has security measures in place to help protect against distributed denial of service (DDoS) attacks. Please bear in mind that if you wish to attempt to test TGModz security measures on your own, we do not allow for any whitelisting. TGModz would request this activity not to be tested as our system has no way of ensuring you are not malicious in nature, your IP address may be Temporarily OR Permanently blocked. TGModz backs up site data on a regular basis, in the event that data loss occurs (like power supply failure or a natural disaster, for example) we can recover it. WordPress uses the wp_users table to store user data in its database. Only the most basic user information is stored here. This includes the username (user_login), password (user_pass), and email (user_email) of the users. WooCommerce uses a combination of both WordPress database tables and its own custom tables to store its data. However, WooCommerce doesn&#8217;t have a dedicated table to store the customer data. The customer data is stored in different database tables, which sometimes might make retrieval of this data challenging. By design, a TGModz customer credit card number and security code are never stored on TGModz. The payment gateway gives this sensitive information directly to the payment processor. We designed our payment gateway to ensure credit card data never enters or passes through TGModz databases.<\/p>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Rights to Your Data<\/h2>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">You have the right to request TGModz for copies of your personal data. You have the right to request that TGModz correct any information you believe is inaccurate. You also have the right to request TGModz to complete the information you believe is incomplete. You have the right to request that TGModz erase your personal data, under certain conditions. You have the right to request that TGModz transfer the data that we have collected to another organization, or directly to you. If you have an account on TGModz, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes. If you make a request, TGModz has one month to respond to you. If you would like to exercise any of these rights, please contact us at our email: contact@tgmodz.com<\/p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/discord.gg\/tgmodz\">Discord<\/a><\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Cookies Cookies are text files placed on your computer to collect standard Internet log information and visitor behavior information. When you visit our websites, we&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":6,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-3","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO Premium plugin v27.0 (Yoast SEO v27.0) - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-premium-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>Privacy Policy - TGModz<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"noindex, follow\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Privacy Policy\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Cookies Cookies are text files placed on your computer to collect standard Internet log information and visitor behavior information. When you visit our websites, we...\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/tgmodz.com\/privacy-policy\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"TGModz\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2023-12-29T15:03:55+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/tgmodz.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/cropped-W.png\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"512\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"512\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image\/png\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<me